#Text=Andrea Muizelaar on fashion , anorexia , and life after ' Top Model '
#Text=Monday , November 26 , 2007
#Text=In the 18 months since Andrea Muizelaar was crowned winner of the reality TV series Canada 's Next Top Model , her life has been a complete whirlwind .
#Text=From working in a dollar store in her hometown of Whitby , Ontario , to modeling haute couture in Toronto , she had reached her dream of becoming a true Top Model .
#Text=But at what cost ?
#Text=Unknown to casual television viewers , Muizelaar had been enveloped in the eating disorder anorexia nervosa , which inevitably became too much for her to bear .
#Text=She gave up modeling and moved back to Whitby , where she sought treatment for her disorder , re-entered college , and now works at a bank .
#Text=Where is she now ? Happy and healthy , she says .

#Text=Recently Andrea Muizelaar sat down with Wikinews reporter Mike Halterman in a candid interview that stretched to nearly two hours , as she told all about her hopes and aspirations , her battle with anorexia , and just what really happened on Canada 's Next Top Model .
#Text=Andrea 's beginnings
#Text=Mike Halterman : Tell us a bit about your background .
#Text=We know all about the Andrea we saw on Top Model , but we 're interested to hear where you came from .
#Text=What do your parents do ?
#Text=Did you have any hard times growing up ?
#Text=Andrea Muizelaar :
#Text=I am from Whitby , Ontario .
#Text=My Dad works in the nuclear industry and my Mom is a stay-at-home mom .
#Text=I had a lot of trouble from my peers at school due to my " geeky " appearance - braces , etc.
#Text=MH : How geeky are we talking here ?
#Text=Worse than any other teenager ?
#Text=AM : Probably not extremely geeky ; more of being a victim of a bully who liked to pick on me continuously and influenced other kids to do likewise .
#Text=MH :
#Text=How long did that last ?
#Text=AM :
#Text=I would say from Grade 2 to Grade 9 .
#Text=MH : What happened after that point ?
#Text=Did they stop , or did you grow into your looks , or was it something else ?
#Text=AM : I definitely grew into my looks , the braces came off ; high school is a bigger place and the bullying subsided because I had new friends .
#Text=MH : This was also around the time you wanted to model , right ?
#Text=AM : Correct .
#Text=Once I transitioned into a pretty young lady , people started telling me that I should model .
#Text=Going from one extreme , to this one , it went to my head and I started dieting over the summer of Grade 9 to make sure that I was the perfect candidate .
#Text=MH : Is that when you first became anorexic ?
#Text=AM : Yes - I lost 20 pounds that summer and then starting losing my control and modelling became my new excuse for this weight loss and soon-to-be disorder .
